node.text: Two specially-crafted decks and t-shirts from @berrics and @everybodyskates are now available exclusively on StockX. Designed by legendary pro @alphonzorawls, this limited ‘Thank You’ collection pays homage to the diversity within skateboarding, featuring the names of influential Black and Brown skateboarders from the last 40 years. Limited quantities are up for grabs, so tap fast to secure yours. A portion of proceeds will support the @nextupfound.

node.text: Travis Scott and fragment design tag teamed a Jordan 1 High collab that blends both their signature aesthetics. OG fans will recognize similarities to the never-released 1985 AJ1 Royal sample with its white and blue tumbled leather upper. The pair features Scott’s signature reverse Swoosh and hidden stash pockets, while co-branding and yellowed midsoles complete the look. Tap to shop.

node.text: The upcoming Jordan 1 High OG Seafoam comes laced in a pastel colorway that’s fit for Spring and Summer looks. Its smooth white leather upper is accented by lightly tumbled overlays, lining, and outsole, each in the titular hue. A final pop of deep orange is featured on two-tone laces. Tap to shop this women’s exclusive early.

node.text: Nike teamed up with San Francisco-based skate shop FTC to deliver an SB Dunk Low inspired by Japanese bathhouses. The collab features a blue suede upper, white quilted overlays, and pops of yellow on the heel tab and liner. FTC branding, silver Swooshes, and an icy translucent outsole complete the look. Tap to shop.
